THE Federal Government has approved the appointment of Abdullahi Ahmed Alhassan as the Rector of the Federal Polytechnic, Nasarawa, Nasarawa State. A statement from the Office of the Minister of Education, Adamu Adamu said, the appointment is with effect from the 31st of December, 2018 and for an initial period of four (4) years. The statement issued by the Deputy Director, Press, Mr Ben Bem Goong on Tuesday indicated Abdullahi Ahmed takes over from Prof. Shatima Abdulkadir Saidu, who has served his four year tenure. ALSO READ: Why I celebrated becoming a US citizen —Laide Bakare Born on the 3rd of March, 1966, Ahmed, holds a National Diploma (ND) in Estate Management, a Higher National Diploma (HND) in Estate Management, Post Graduate Diploma in Land Administration, Master of Science (MSc) degree in Land Resources Administration, Master of Philosophy (MPhil) in Geography (Environmental Resource Management) and a Doctor of Philosophy (PhD) Environmental Science, in view. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that
